<exercise checkit-seed="0007" checkit-slug="AD1" checkit-title="Tangents, Motion, and Marginals">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                Let <m>h(x) = -2 \, x^{4} + 2 \, x^{3} - x - 1</m>. Find an equation of the line tangent to the graph at the point <m>(2, -19)</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
        <p>
Suppose the position of an object in kilometers
is modeled by the following function.
<me>s(t)=t^{3} + 2 \, t^{2} - 3 \, t - 18</me>
        </p>
        <p>
Explain how to find the object's position, displacement,
velocity, speed, and acceleration at <m>3</m>
seconds. Use appropriate units for each.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
A thingamajig is sold for <m>\$385</m> per item.
The cost (in dollars) of manufacturing <m>x</m> items is given by the
following function:
<me>C(x)=2 \, x^{3} + 5 \, x^{2} + 7 \, x + 6</me>
                </p>
                <p>
Suppose that the number of items produced is equal to the number of items sold. 
Explain how to find the marginal revenue, the marginal cost, and the marginal profit
for this situation.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
The equation of the tangent line is <m>y = -41 \, x + 63</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
                    
            <li>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
Position: <m>18</m> kilometers
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Displacement: <m>36</m> kilometers
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Velocity: <m>36</m> kilometers per second
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Speed: <m>36</m> kilometers per second
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Acceleration: <m>22</m> kilometers per <m>s^2</m>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
The marginal cost is <m>6 \, x^{2} + 10 \, x + 7</m>,
the marginal revenue is <m>385</m>,
and the marginal profit is <m>-6 \, x^{2} - 10 \, x + 378</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
